==Group stage==
{{Main|2013 CECAFA Cup group stage}}
The group stage began on 27 November and ended on 5 December. The matchdays were 27<U+2013>29 November, 30 November<U+2013>2 December and 3<U+2013>5 December.

<div id="Tiebreakers">
If two or more teams were equal on points on completion of the group matches, the following criteria were applied to determine the rankings (in descending order):
{{col-begin}}
{{col-2}}
# Number of points obtained in games between the teams involved;
# Goal difference in games between the teams involved;
# Goals scored in games between the teams involved;
# Away goals scored in games between the teams involved;
# Goal difference in all games;
# Goals scored in all games;
# Drawing of lots.
{{col-2}}
{| class="wikitable"
|-
! Key to colours in group tables
|-bgcolor="#ccffcc"
| Group winners and runners-up advance to the [[#Knockout stage|quarter-finals]]
|-bgcolor="#ccccff"
| Third-placed teams to be ranked for advancement to the [[#Knockout stage|quarter-finals]]
|-bgcolor="#ffcccc"
| Team already eliminated
|}
{{col-end}}

===Group A===
Since [[Kenya national football team|Kenya]] and [[Ethiopia national football team|Ethiopia]] had the same statistics at the end of the group stage, a coin toss was used as the drawing of lots to determine the winner of Group A.<ref name="Group A coin toss">{{cite news |url=http://www.futaa.com/football/article/kenya-wins-group-a-toss |title=Kenya wins Group A toss |author=Dan Ngulu |publisher=Futaa.com |date=5 December 2013 |accessdate=10 December 2013}}</ref>
